article.headline: Biden won't go to Democratic convention in Milwaukee: report
article.body: Presumptive Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden will not travel to Milwaukee, Wisc., to accept the nomination at his party convention's this month due to concerns about the coronavirus, according to a Bloomberg report on Wednesday citing people familiar with the matter. Biden had been expected to accept the nomination in Milwaukee, but the party has been urging delegates to skip the convention because of coronavirus concerns.
